column_contents: From Clingmans Dome Parking Area follow paved trail towards the lookout tower.  Past the visitor center about 0.2 mile  there is a concrete bench on the right side of the trail. The next tree is a Red Spruce with a diameter of 50.2 cm at 25 degrees.  This Spruce is on the ridge.  The next Spruce is about 30 meters at 38 degrees with a diameter of 23 cm. From this tree the top right corner of the hectare ATBI Plot is 55 degrees at about 25 meters.  This corner is marked with a thin red electric fence post about 3 feet tall.  All tree tags are marked "ATBI".  The hectare is marked off with nylon string around the parameter.  The Long Term Monitoring Plot is also marked with string.  Do not disturb the Long Term Monitoring Plot.

question: Show me the events where both nested subplots and decayed logs were observed. Include the number of decayed logs, and the number of nested subplots were observed.
text: Show me the events where both nested subplots and decayed logs were observed. Include the number of decayed logs, and the number of nested subplots were observed.
sql: SELECT e.Event_ID, Deadwood_Count, Nest_Count  FROM tbl_Events AS e JOIN (     SELECT Event_ID, COUNT(*) AS Deadwood_Count     FROM tbl_Deadwood     GROUP BY Event_ID ) AS dw ON e.Event_ID = dw.Event_ID JOIN (     SELECT Event_ID, COUNT(*) AS Nest_Count     FROM tbl_Nests     GROUP BY Event_ID ) AS ne ON e.Event_ID = ne.Event_ID order by Deadwood_Count desc

column_contents: From Clingmans Dome Parking Area follow paved trail towards the lookout tower.  Past the visitor center about 0.2 mile  there is a concrete bench on the right side of the trail.  This bench is the first reference point to a Red Spruce with a diameter of 21.2 cm.  It is about 50 meters at 20 degrees from the bench..  The next tree is a Red Spruce with a diameter of 50.2 cm at 25 degrees.  This Spruce is on the ridge.  The next Spruce is about 30 meters at 38 degrees with a diameter of 23 cm. From this tree the top right corner of the hectare ATBI Plot is 55 degrees at about 25 meters.  This corner is marked with a thin red electric fence post about 3 feet tall.  All tree tags are marked "ATBI".  The hectare is marked off with nylon string around the parameter.  The Long Term Monitoring Plot is also marked with string.  Do not disturb the Long Term Monitoring Plot.

The wrong subspecies of Amakihi was entered for 2017 HALE Amakihi detections.Chlorodrepanis virens virens was entered for 2017 HALE bird detections when the correct subspecies is Chlorodrepanis virens wilsoni.
Moving forward bird surveys on Maui will be in cooperation with partners, so need to have all the bird data together in the database.  Non-NPS data will not be released to the public.

Imported the 2017 non-HALE Maui Forest Bird Recovery Project stations and data into the database.

Moving forward bird surveys on Maui will be in cooperation with partners, so need to have all the bird data together in the database.  Non-NPS data will not be released to the public.

question: What percent of stations has the bird with the common name Hawaii Amakihi been observed at?
text: What percent of stations has the bird with the common name Hawaii Amakihi been observed at?
sql: select 100 * (sum(sighted) / count(distinct station_id)) as perc_stations from ( 	select distinct tbl_stations.station_id, case  			when tlu_species.common_name = 'Hawaii Amakihi' then 1.0 else 0.0 			end as sighted 	from tbl_stations 	join tbl_events on tbl_stations.station_id = tbl_events.station_id 	join tbl_observations on tbl_observations.event_id = tbl_events.event_id 	join tlu_species on tlu_species.species_id = tbl_observations.species_id ) sightings

question: What is the average canopy height of each species' habitats? Include the common name and scientfic name of each species. Ensure the average has decimal precision.
text: What is the average canopy height of each species' habitats? Include the common name and scientfic name of each species. Ensure the average has decimal precision.
sql: select Scientific_Name, Common_Name, avg(cast(canopy_height as float)) as avg_canopy_height from tbl_habitat hab join tbl_events ev on hab.Event_ID = ev.Event_ID join tbl_Observations obs on obs.Event_ID = ev.Event_ID join tlu_species spec on spec.species_id = obs.species_id group by Scientific_Name, common_name order by Scientific_Name

question: Which island has the most sightings of the bird with the common name Pacific Kingfisher?
text: Which island has the most sightings of the bird with the common name Pacific Kingfisher?
sql: select top 1 island, count(*) as kingfisher_count from tbl_locations tl join tbl_transect tr on tr.Location_ID = tl.Location_ID join tbl_stations st on st.Transect_ID = tr.Transect_ID join tbl_events te on te.station_id = st.station_id join xref_Event_Contacts ec on ec.Event_ID = te.Event_ID join tlu_Contacts con on ec.Contact_ID = con.Contact_ID join tbl_Observations obs on te.Event_ID = obs.Event_ID join tlu_species spc on obs.Species_ID = spc.Species_ID where common_name = 'Pacific Kingfisher' group by island order by kingfisher_count
